public static void createTestData()

collectionEquals

public static <E> boolean collectionEquals(Collection<E> c1,
                                           Collection<E> c2)
Returns true if two collections contain the same elements. The order in which the elements are retrieved does not matter, if an element is contained multiple times it must be contained multiple times in the other collection as well.

Type Parameters:
E - an arbitrary type.
Parameters:
c1 - a collection
c2 - a collection
Returns:
if the given collections contain the same elements
